### REST Client file for VS Code
### Install "REST Client" extension to run these directly from the editor.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/v1

### 1. Test the POST /tenants Endpoint (Success Case)
# This should now return { success: true, data: { ... } }
POST {{baseUrl}}/tenants
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "business_name": "Test Pharmacy",
  "tenant_slug": "test-pharmacy",
  "owner_name": "John Doe",
  "username": "johndoe",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 2. Test the POST /tenants Endpoint (Validation Error Case)
# This should return our custom { success: false, error: { code: '...', message: [...] } }
# It fails because the password is too weak and the slug has invalid characters.
POST {{baseUrl}}/tenants
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "business_name": "Bad Pharmacy",
  "tenant_slug": "bad_slug!!",
  "owner_name": "Jane Doe",
  "username": "jane",
  "password": "123"
}

### 3. Test POST /auth/sessions (Login)
# Replace credentials if needed. Should return { success: true, data: { access_token: "..." } }
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "johndoe",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 4. Test GET /tenants/me (Auth Required)
# Remember to replace the token below with the one returned from the login request!
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Test Unauthorized Access
# Should return { success: false, error: { code: 'Unauthorized', message: 'Unauthorized' } }
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me
